Thank you [~pvary] for pinging me! :)
please don't do this in "setup()":

{code}
-      qt.newSession();
+      qt.clearTestSideEffects();
{code}

this will restore the old erratic behaviour which is: the "next" test will try to cleanup after the previous one; which would be a step backward...
{{qt.clearTestSideEffects}} should belong to the after ...if you would like to have a way to leave the tables/databases behind; please add an option or something which prevents cleanup...

Maybe I'm just skeptical; but I don't believe that adding a builder would make qtestutil any better - I think instead of trying to fix qtestutil; we should roll some new stuff...but it's fine by me as long as it works...
but if you are introducing it...you might want to consider using it to hide away configuration decisions..like: "if (testArgs.getFsType() != null)"
